  "instructions": [
    "Preheat your oven to 275°F (135°C).",
    "Season the lamb shoulder with salt, black pepper, and red pepper flakes.",
    "Heat the olive oil in a large copper mug over medium-high heat.",
    "Sear the lamb shoulder until browned on all sides, about 2 minutes per side.",
    "Transfer the lamb to the preheated oven and roast for 3 hours, or until the meat is tender and falls apart easily.",
    "Remove the lamb from the oven and let it rest for 10 minutes.",
    "Sprinkle the chopped parsley over the top of the lamb and serve."
